de>System.getProperty</code> except that the\r\n     * {@link SecurityException} is absorbed.\r\n     *\r\n     * @param key The key to search for.\r\n     * @return the string value of the system property.\r\n     */\r\n    public static String getSystemProperty(String key) {\r\n        try {\r\n            return System.getProperty(key);\r\n        } catch (SecurityException e) {\r\n            return null;\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public static void setSystemProperties(ContextAware contextAware, Properties props) {\r\n        for (Object o : props.keySet()) {\r\n            String key = (String) o;\r\n            String value = props.getProperty(key);\r\n            setSystemProperty(contextAware, key, value);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public static void setSystemProperty(ContextAware contextAware, String key, String value) {\r\n        try {\r\n            System.setProperty(key, value);\r\n\n[107 more lines in file. Use offset=221 to continue.]"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777641475737}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test requirements**\n\nI’m planning a test without reflection and using a public API. The PropertyEvalScriptBuilder directly generates classes and depends on Janino and Commons Compiler, which are included in build.gradle. I need to think about using Native Image, as Janino may trigger an UnsupportedFeatureError at runtime. If that happens in a native context, I’ll need to catch it in the test. I should consider whether metadata for generated classes is necessary since dynamic loading isn't supported in native.\n\n**Evaluating native compilation**\n\nWhen compiling natively, the Janino class generated at test runtime isn’t present during the image build. I wonder if the agent records the reflection config with unusual names. It's possible metadata generation during tests isn't happening, especially since the tests may not run the agent. The native compile might analyze code paths without executing tests. If runtime doesn’t support Janino class loading, reflection will fail. I might need to catch errors and utilize `PropertyEvalScriptBuilder` properly by setting the context for property availability.\n\n**Checking context implementation**\n\nI think I need to verify that `Context` extends `PropertyContainer` and utilize `ContextBase`. I should evaluate some checks to see if the context is null when not set, as `OptionHelper` might handle this. I need to assert that the invocation of `set` on property containers is successful. To confirm that `setMapMethod.invoke` worked, the script should read properties from the local or context. If it wasn’t invoked, could it lead to a NullPointerException? I should check if `OptionHelper` is looking up properties correctly with the local context.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d3dc4a25cf3f3c20169f4a7f8e12081a2a0737f4898dbeea7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9KgDEcaJJAXOmKgrl_bhDP6